 there are no time restrictions up to 24 hours. Locations stretch between Deira through to Palm Jumeirah. Byke rentals start from AED 15 for 30 minutes, AED 20 for 1 hour and AED 80 for 24 hours.<br><br>Bus stations:<br>The Dubai bus service network, covers 87% of the urban area in the Emirate of Dubai. The bus service is designed in such a way that it makes each corner of Dubai easy and accessible with a total of 125 Dubai bus routes. The routes offer 48 local services, 31 feeder buses, 13 central business district services, 8 express services, 11 inter-city service buses and 3 buses to key destinations such as Global village and Miracle Garden.<br><br>Dubai Tram:<br>The Dubai tramway covers a distance of 10.6 Km and is located in Al Sufouh, Dubai. The tram runs between 11 stations that includes Al Sufouh Road, Dubai Marina, Palm Jumeirah and Jumeirah Lakes Towers. The Dubai Tram is also the first tramway project outside of Europe that is powered by a ground-based electric supply system.<br><br>Marine:<br>In pursuit of RTA’s efforts to serve every corner of Dubai’s population, the RTA has created a modern style of public transport under the umbrella of Marine Transportation. This mode of transportation encourages the public and tourists to take an alternative approach to view the city with multiple offerings such as: an Abra, RTA Water bus, RTA water taxi and Dubai Ferry.</p>
